Marketing Cookies
Off
We use these cookies to promote Consumer Reports’ own products and services that are relevant to your interests. We also use cookies to serve ads for CR Products on other websites you visit. We may also send you emails or other communications regarding CR Products. For example, if you view car-related content on CR.org, you may see an ad or receive an email or other communication about our Build & Buy Car Buying Service. Consumer Reports does not accept third-party advertising. You can turn off these cookies by switching the above toggle to “Off” and clicking the “Save Settings” button below.
You can also accept these cookie by clicking the ‘Allow All’ button below.
Additionally, you can opt out of interest-based advertising, as well as advertising on your mobile device, by visiting our
Ad Choices manager
or our cookie management tool described below.
